Timothy M. Ring, chairman and chief executive officer, commented, "Despite a challenging quarter in our hernia fixation business, we continue to deliver healthy earnings. These results demonstrate the benefits of a diverse product portfolio and the strength of our vascular, urology and oncology franchises. Our focus remains on sustaining growth through the execution of our R&D and business development strategies."
