"Debt"
"" means generally accepted accounting principles set forth in the FASB Accounting Standards Codification or in such other statements by such other entity as may be approved by a significant segment of the accounting profession of the United States, as in effect from time to time. At any time after the initial date of issuance of the Notes, the Company may elect (by providing written notice to the trustee) to apply International Financial Reporting Standards ("") in lieu of GAAP and, upon any such election, references herein to GAAP shall thereafter be construed to mean IFRS (except as otherwise provided herein); that any such election, once made, shall be irrevocable.
