 (July 21, 2011)  C. R. Bard, Inc. (NYSE: BCR) today reported 2011 second quarter financial results. Second quarter 2011 net sales were $725.0 million, an increase of 8 percent over the prior-year period on a reported basis, 5 percent on a constant currency basis.
MURRAY HILL, NJ
For the second quarter 2011, net sales in the U.S. were $479.9 million, an increase of 3 percent. Net sales outside the U.S. were $245.1 million, an increase of 17 percent on a reported basis, 10 percent on a constant currency basis.
